Program: Discovery
Title: Breast and ovarian cancer gene breakthrough
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx87
Last Broadcast Date: 16 November 1998
The discovery of a gene that causes breast and ovarian cancer. Scientists are using the models of the BRAC1 genetic mutations in a breakthrough that could lead to treatment. Also in the programme, the coldest atoms on earth that reach absolute zero and the wonder of neurology.